Usage:
 <nowiki>{{Coin specification table row
   |imageobverse   =
   |imagereverse   =
   |imagewidth     =
   |value          =
   |diameter       =
   |thickness      =
   |mass           =
   |coincolor      =
 [ |composition    =  [ |composition_span       = ] ]
 [ |descobverse    =  [ |descobverse_span       = ] ]
 [ |descreverse    =  [ |descreverse_span       = ] ]
 [ |descedge       =  [ |descedge_span          = ] ]
   |dateminting    =
   |dateissue      =
   |datewithdrawal =
 [ |remark         =  [ |remark_span =            ] ]
 }}</nowiki>

说明：
* ''imageobverse''和''imagereverse''分别填硬币正面和背面的图像的名称；
* ''imagewidth''为''width'' × 3；
* ''value''指硬币的面值；
* ''diameter'' and ''thickness'' are coin dimensions in millimeters;
* ''mass'' is coin weight in grams;
* ''composition'' describes the metals and/or alloys used (see note below);
* ''coincolor'' is either ''silver'', ''copper'', ''yellow'' (default ''silver'');
* ''descobverse'', ''descreverse'' and ''descedge'' are descriptions of obverse, reverse and edge (see note below),
* ''dateminting'', ''dateissue'' and ''datewithdrawal'' are dates of first minting, issue and withdrawal.
* ''remark'' adds general description of the design or minor minting variants, or describes specific usages of the coin (see note below).

All the parameters above are normally required, except those with the "_span" extension (whose default value is 1): to create more compact tables where long descriptive fields are should span several rows,
* supply the parameter value only for the first displayed row,
* and give the number of successive coins to which the same description applies in the optional parameter with the "_span" extension,
* then remove the description parameter from the other rows.
When spanning is not used in a page using this template, don't supply the "_span" parameters but keep all the other parameters.

